<P><h2>Hearing problem</h2>
<img src="https://s3-us-east-2.amazonaws.com/maryville/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/01154035/MVU-Skyscraper-3-Hearing-Loss-Types-header-v3.jpg?hl=en_US" width="250" height="250" alt="knee problem">
<br>A cochlear implant is a small electronic device that can help improve the hearing of people with severe,
<br> irreversible hearing loss. Although a cochlear implant does not restore normal hearing,
<br> it can allow a person to hear and understand more speech than was possible with a hearing aid.</p>
<p><h2>Knee problem</h2>
<img src="https://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/-/media/images/health/2_-treatment/orthopedics/knee-pain-teaser.ashx?hl=en_US" width="250" height="250" alt="knee problem">
<br>Mild knee injuries often improve with rest, ice and anti-inflammatory medications. 
<br>Wearing a brace can stabilize your knee while it recovers. If arthritis is causing knee pain,
<br> your treatment may include medication and physical therapy.</p>
