<h2>Heart issue</h2>
<img src="https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1128931450/photo/heart-attack-concept.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=XHOhTXhpZMSV6XIhXLbH6uvNQjZQS93b1UetGfqQXtI=&hl=en_US" width="250" height="250" alt="heart problem">
Try to limit saturated fats, foods high in sodium, and added sugars. Eat plenty of fresh fruit, vegetables, 
<br>and whole grains. The DASH diet is an example of an eating plan that can help you to lower your blood pressure and cholesterol,
<br>two things that can lower your risk of heart disease. Get regular exercise.</p>
